{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d4d2ca24-41c1-4a27-80c4-cc89cb7cf19a","content":"## Diagnosis\n\n**.NET MAUI's Android build toolchain does not use `JAVA_HOME`**. It has its own JDK discovery logic (via the `$(JavaSdkDirectory)` MSBuild property) and expects the **Microsoft build of OpenJDK 17** that ships with the android workload — not Temurin.\n\n## Fix (pick one)\n\n**Option A — Install Microsoft OpenJDK 17 (recommended):**\n```bash\nbrew install --cask microsoft-openjdk-17\n```\nThe MAUI build will auto-discover it at `/Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines/microsoft-17.jdk/Contents/Home`.\n\n**Option B — Point the build at your Temurin JDK explicitly:**\n\nAdd to your `.csproj`:\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup Condition=\"'$(TargetFramework)' == 'net8.0-android' or '$(TargetFramework)' == 'net9.0-android'\">\n  <JavaSdkDirectory>$(JAVA_HOME)</JavaSdkDirectory>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nOr pass it on the command line:\n```bash\ndotnet build -p:JavaSdkDirectory=\"$JAVA_HOME\"\n```\n\n**Option A** is the path of least resistance — it's what the toolchain is tested against and avoids any subtle distribution differences.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"faaf5034-07aa-47e7-9469-afef2470dbf9","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a .NET MAUI Android build failure related to Java. They have Adoptium Temurin JDK 17.0.12 installed. Let me think about what the common issue is here.\n\nThis is a well-known issue: .NET MAUI / Xamarin Android builds require a specific JDK. Starting with .NET 8+, the Android SDK build tools require JDK 17, but there's a specific issue with .NET MAUI and Java compatibility.\n\nActually, the most common issue is that .NET MAUI Android builds (particularly with newer versions) require JDK 17, but the key issue is often about the specific JDK distribution or version compatibility.\n \nThe problem is likely that .NET MAUI expects Microsoft OpenJDK by default and looks for it in specific paths through the MSBuild `$